<br>
I stare at the quill, ink, and new spellbook wondering if this is right. I look back at my old spellbook the pages held in by glue and luck. Wondering how I ever managed to keep it all these many years. I open my new spellbook and begin to write slowly scribing the spells word by word onto the pages. Copying from my old spellbook placing the spells into a new order, knowing that I will forever be searching for the spells I need now.<br>
<br>
I lean back against the tree as I write, remembering the first time I cast a teleport at level 19. The first time I soloed a Hillgiant at 25. The first time I teleported my friends at 29. Smiling I continue to copy down the spells the pages in my old book seeming to crumble as I scribe the spell into the new book. With each spell comes a new memory, sometimes sad but always strong. <br>
<br>
As I reach the last pages of my old spell book I hold the old worn leather book in my hands and stare at the last spell that is before me and cry. I begin to copy that spell into my new book, watching as the page crumbles with every word I write. Feeling years of memories flooding my mind.<br>
<br>
As I write the last words into the new book I feel the power transfer from the old book to the new. The old book slowly crumbles falling to the ground at my feet. I sit back and look at my new spell book the power that it possess and the new order that has. I slip the book into my pack and smile. Knowing that the memories will always be there with me. <br>
<br>
I chuckle as I think back to that gnome laughing as he sold me my book. I look up into the sky and know there are many new journeys ahead of me. I lay my head down in the grass and think about the past and smile as I fall asleep. <p><center>
